Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it from sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

When there are 5 mins left of pasta cooking time remaining, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g}(halved) to the pan and cook for the remaining time.

While the pasta and broccoli cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop both the @olives{30%g}(roughly chopped) and @capers{15%g}(roughly chopped).

== Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Next, stir-fry the garlic and @chilli flakes{1%pinch} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @finely chopped tomatoes{1/2%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, olives, capers, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce into the pan. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, lower the heat to medium and stir through the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{}, or a pinch of sugar if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little too thick.

== To Finish ==

When the sauce is ready, add the cooked rigatoni, broccoli and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} to the pan. Stir and toss well to combine.

Share your puttanesca style bacon pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Enjoy!